reviewText: Although this DVD is a bit dated it helped my son tremendously with learning colors, shapes, alphabet.  Even my 7 year old watches it in the car and sings the songs. It has kid songs for colors, numbers, and alphabet which seem to stick in your head.  Very cute with low production and dated but still valuable learning.

reviewText: My 2.5 yr old loved this movie. He laughed so hard and danced and sung to the entire thing. He learned letters, animals and numbers. Its a great value and left my son wanting more. Great investment.
summary: My 2.5 yr old son LOVED it.

reviewText: This DVD is very good and keeps my toddler son's attention very well.  It has some of the other Rock 'N Learn DVD material in it and for such a great price!  This DVD alone has taught my son letter recognition of half the alphabet and sounding some of the letters out in only about 3 weeks..him being 19 months old.  The DVD is fun, entertaining and well worth it.  I bought this DVD for other family members too who have preschoolers and they all enjoy it as well!  Would definitely recommend!It includes titles (all of which are on their other DVD series)1. Alphabet Al Goes to the Circus [28:55]2. Alphabet Al's Name Game [3:08]3. The Alphabet Song [1:10]4. Learn About Animals [30:10]5. Fun With Jill and Joey [13:19]6. Songs About Colors [7:55]7. Fun With Shapes [5:54]8. Practice Counting [3:59]9. Count to 20 in Spanish [4:05]10. Favorite Rhymes [19:42]
summary: Great Bargain for the amount of learning material!
